544
00:31:56.505 --> 00:31:57.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>I thought it might be a good idea</i></c.bg_transparent>

545
00:31:57.824 --> 00:31:59.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>to go through</i></c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent><i>all the communications logs</i></c.bg_transparent>

546
00:31:59.784 --> 00:32:01.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>from headquarters during that period.</i></c.bg_transparent>

547
00:32:01.903 --> 00:32:04.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>I even found Curzon Dax's records.</i></c.bg_transparent>

548
00:32:04.662 --> 00:32:07.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent>You can't tell me Curzon</c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent>would log in a communiqué to the enemy.</c.bg_transparent>

549
00:32:07.902 --> 00:32:09.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>No, nothing like that,</i></c.bg_transparent>

550
00:32:09.381 --> 00:32:11.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>but the log does show</i></c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent><i>a number of conversations</i></c.bg_transparent>

551
00:32:12.601 --> 00:32:15.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>between Dax's office</i></c.bg_transparent>
<c.bg_transparent><i>and General Tandro's home.</i></c.bg_transparent>

552
00:32:15.379 --> 00:32:16.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<c.bg_transparent>They were close friends.</c.bg_transparent>

553
00:32:16.738 --> 00:32:20.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<c.bg_transparent><i>A number of the conversations took place</i></c.bg_transparent>
